linked to an improved supply outlook and to recession fears fueled 
by the stock markets erratic moves which included sharp drops on 
tuesday thursday and friday 
copper is heavily used in construction and industrial 
applications and a weaker economy would reduce demand for the metal 
copper for december delivery settled friday at 11580 a pound 
compared with 12345 a week earlier and 13050 the week before 
that 
</TEXT>
